(Marimba CNC Bar And Resonator Build Packet - page 2 of 20) Tj T*
( ) Tj T*
(| Instrument family | Free-free beam idiophone with tuned quarter-wave resonators |) Tj T*
(| Active build range | C3-C6 chromatic, 37 bars |) Tj T*
(| Source workbook | marimba-design-table.xlsx, sheet Marimba, range A1:X106 |) Tj T*
(| Primary material | African Padauk bars, workbook K constant 155502 |) Tj T*
(| Bar thickness | 0.875 in nominal edge thickness |) Tj T*
(| Minimum center thickness | 0.250 in after arch undercut |) Tj T*
(| Construction pipeline | CNC surfaced blanks, 3D arch undercut, profile/tabs, node) Tj T*
(drilling, resonator cutting, frame assembly |) Tj T*
(| Done-bar reference | tongue-drum README and wooden idiophone validation discipline |) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The guided v4.2 intake artifacts are in data/design-intake.json and data/design-input-) Tj T*
(row.csv.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Governing Model) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Bar Pitch) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The marimba bars are treated as free-free beams. The first flexural mode uses:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(    lambda_1 = 4.730) Tj T*
(    f_1 = \(lambda_1^2 / \(2piL^2\)\)  sqrt\(EI/\(rhoA\)\)) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The workbook uses the practical shop form:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(    f ~= K  t / L^2) Tj T*
(    L ~= sqrt\(K  t / f\)) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(where:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- f is target frequency in Hz.) Tj T*
(- K is the material-specific free-free bar constant.) Tj T*
(- t is nominal bar thickness at the edge.) Tj T*
(- L is bar length.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(For the active packet:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(    K = 155502) Tj T*
(    t = 0.875 in) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The workbook material library derives this free-free K from the beam material properties and) Tj T*
(the lambda_1 = 4.730 mode shape. Do not apply flute-bore K2 corrections here; those belong) Tj T*
(to Native American style flute bore correction work, not beam idiophones.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Nodes And Supports) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The suspension node locations are:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(    node_1 = 0.224  L) Tj T*
(    node_2 = 0.776  L) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Cord holes and rail pins reference these two locations. Holes must be drilled at the nodal) Tj T*
(line so the support does not damp the main mode.) Tj T*
ET
endstream
