(Marimba CNC Bar And Resonator Build Packet - page 4 of 20) Tj T*
( ) Tj T*
(1. Cut resonators at least 0.5 in long for C5 and above, and at least 1.0 in long below C5.) Tj T*
(2. Use adjustable caps or removable plugs for the first build.) Tj T*
(3. Tune resonators after the bars are struck and measured in the frame.) Tj T*
(4. Record final tube length and cents response in validation.csv.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Hardware Alignment) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The support rails follow the node path rather than a fixed straight rail. For each bar:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Left support: node_1_in.) Tj T*
(- Right support: node_2_in.) Tj T*
(- Cord/support hole diameter: 0.250 in starting point.) Tj T*
(- Frame pin/rubber support must touch at the node, not at the bar end.) Tj T*
(- Bar spacing and frame taper are TBD until mallet clearance and resonator tube diameters) Tj T*
(are chosen.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( SolidWorks MasterLayout Plan) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The SolidWorks model should be driven from a master sketch and equations:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. A Master_Bar part with configurations from cad/design-table-inputs.csv.) Tj T*
(2. A Master_Resonator part with tube length, bore, cap allowance, and mounting hole) Tj T*
(variables.) Tj T*
(3. A Frame_MasterLayout sketch defining bass and treble rail curves, bar spacing, resonator) Tj T*
(centerlines, and player-side datum.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Do not model hand-edited dimensions in SolidWorks. Every repeated note configuration should) Tj T*
(be driven by the variables listed in cad/sw-global-variables.csv.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Open Assumptions) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Active packet uses C3-C6 instead of the workbook's full C2-F6 or portable C4-F6 variants.) Tj T*
(- African Padauk is the workbook-selected material; actual board availability and moisture) Tj T*
(content are not verified.) Tj T*
(- Resonator tube material and exact bore are TBD; current resonator lengths use the workbook) Tj T*
(width/end-correction proxy.) Tj T*
(- Frame geometry, rail spacing, bar spacing, and transport strategy need CAD and ergonomic) Tj T*
(review.) Tj T*
(- CNC feeds/speeds are starting notes only; final CAM must use the actual bit, router, hold-) Tj T*
(down, stock, and simulation.) Tj T*
(- No measured bar data exists yet, so all frequencies are target predictions.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Validation Plan) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. Surface three sacrificial bars first: C3, A4, and C6. These bound the length, arch, and) Tj T*
(treble-end assumptions.) Tj T*
(2. Measure blank thickness, length, density estimate, and moisture content before cutting) Tj T*
(the arch.) Tj T*
(3. Record flat-bar pitch, post-arch pitch, post-sanding pitch, and final assembled pitch.) Tj T*
(4. Update validation.csv with measured Hz and cents error:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(    cents = 1200  log2\(measured_hz / target_hz\)) Tj T*
ET
endstream
