(Marimba CNC Bar And Resonator Build Packet - page 9 of 20) Tj T*
( ) Tj T*
(- [ ] Print or open drawings/arch-undercut-section.svg, drawings/resonator-layout.svg, and) Tj T*
(cnc/setup-sheet.md.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Bar Workflow) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. Break down rough Padauk stock into oversize blanks using cut-list.csv.) Tj T*
(2. Joint one face and edge. Mark grain direction and top face.) Tj T*
(3. Plane or sand each blank to 0.875 in nominal edge thickness.) Tj T*
(4. Label every blank with member_id, note, target Hz, and top face.) Tj T*
(5. CNC profile each bar oversize or leave tabs for final cleanup.) Tj T*
(6. Mark node positions from family-spec.csv.) Tj T*
(7. Drill support/cord holes at the node line. Start with 0.250 in, then adapt to the actual) Tj T*
(cord/rubber support system.) Tj T*
(8. Cut the underside parabolic arch. Use a conservative Z-zero and leave a sanding/tuning) Tj T*
(allowance.) Tj T*
(9. Deburr and sand without rounding node contact areas excessively.) Tj T*
(10. Strike-test on soft supports at the node positions and record measured Hz in) Tj T*
(validation.csv.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Tuning Direction) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- To lower pitch: remove material from the center underside arch region.) Tj T*
(- To raise pitch: shorten the bar or reduce mass near the ends; raising pitch after over-) Tj T*
(cutting is limited, so sneak up slowly.) Tj T*
(- Keep both ends visually balanced. Asymmetric mass removal can pull modes sideways or) Tj T*
(create uneven sustain.) Tj T*
(- Tune bars before final resonator matching.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Resonator Workflow) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. Select tube material and bore.) Tj T*
(2. Recalculate tube lengths if the selected bore differs from resonator_bore_in.) Tj T*
(3. Cut tubes oversize per cut-list.csv.) Tj T*
(4. Deburr both ends.) Tj T*
(5. Add removable caps or adjustable stoppers.) Tj T*
(6. Mount under the matching bar with the opening centered below the vibrating region.) Tj T*
(7. Trim or adjust caps after the bar pitch is stable in the frame.) Tj T*
(8. Record final resonator length, cap style, and response notes.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Frame Workflow) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. Build a temporary straight or lightly tapered validation frame before the final) Tj T*
(furniture-grade frame.) Tj T*
(2. Lay out rail supports from the node schedule, not from equal bar-end offsets.) Tj T*
(3. Keep resonator access open so tubes can be removed and tuned.) Tj T*
(4. Add cross members only after checking mallet clearance, tube clearance, and player reach.) Tj T*
(5. Use removable fasteners until tuning and buzz checks are done.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Final Checks) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- [ ] All bars are labeled and match family-spec.csv.) Tj T*
(- [ ] Node supports touch at node positions.) Tj T*
ET
endstream
endobj
