(Marimba CNC Bar And Resonator Build Packet - page 14 of 20) Tj T*
( ) Tj T*
(suspended at their nodes, with a matched resonator under each note. It turns the existing) Tj T*
(marimba-design-table.xlsx scaffold into a shop-facing documentation set:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. design.md explains the physics model, build range, assumptions, and validation plan.) Tj T*
(2. family-spec.csv is the 37-bar C3-C6 schedule extracted from the workbook formulas.) Tj T*
(3. bom.csv, sourcing.csv, and cut-list.csv separate stable specifications from supplier) Tj T*
(facts that should be verified before buying.) Tj T*
(4. drawings/, cad/, cnc/, wolfram/, and site/ carry the technical handoff layers.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Part of the tonykoop/instrument-maker catalog.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Physics In One Minute) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(A marimba bar is a free-free beam. The first mode uses lambda_1 = 4.730, and the practical) Tj T*
(workbook model is:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(    f ~= K  t / L^2) Tj T*
(    L ~= sqrt\(K  t / f\)) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Length is the dominant pitch lever. Bar thickness and the underside arch tune the bar; width) Tj T*
(mostly affects feel, loudness, stiffness distribution, and available resonator bore. The) Tj T*
(cord/support points land at about 0.224  L and 0.776  L.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The resonator tubes are quarter-wave closed pipes:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(    L_res ~= c / \(4  f\) - 0.82  bore) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The resonator reinforces the bar's target frequency. It does not tune the bar itself.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Build Range) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The active packet is a 37-bar chromatic range from C3 to C6, using the workbook's African) Tj T*
(Padauk setting:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(| Note | Frequency | Bar length | Width | Arch depth | Resonator |) Tj T*
(| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |) Tj T*
(| C3 | 130.813 Hz | 32.251 in | 2.000 in | 0.625 in | 24.260 in |) Tj T*
(| C4 | 261.626 Hz | 22.805 in | 1.750 in | 0.469 in | 11.515 in |) Tj T*
(| A4 | 440.000 Hz | 17.585 in | 1.750 in | 0.352 in | 6.265 in |) Tj T*
(| C6 | 1046.502 Hz | 11.403 in | 1.250 in | 0.156 in | 2.212 in |) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The workbook also documents two expansion shapes: a full C2-F6 marimba and a portable C4-F6) Tj T*
(instrument. Those are not cut lists yet; they are future configurations once the C3-C6 bar) Tj T*
(and resonator workflow is validated.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Repository Structure) Tj T*
