( Acoustic Risks) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Bar pitch misses workbook prediction) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Risk: The selected Padauk stock has a different effective stiffness/density than the) Tj T*
(workbook K constant.) Tj T*
(- Impact: All bars may cut sharp or flat by a consistent amount.) Tj T*
(- Test: Cut and measure C3, A4, and C6 pilot bars before the full run.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: Post-arch bars can be brought within +/- 10 cents by normal sanding/tuning) Tj T*
(allowance.) Tj T*
(- Mitigation: Update K constant or arch schedule before cutting the remaining bars.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Resonator bore proxy is wrong) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Risk: The workbook currently uses bar width as the resonator bore/end-correction proxy.) Tj T*
(- Impact: Tube lengths may be wrong after real tube diameters are selected.) Tj T*
(- Test: Select actual tube ID, recalculate C3/A4/C6 resonator lengths, and compare response.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: Resonator reinforcement peaks near target pitch without strong buzz or) Tj T*
(deadening.) Tj T*
(- Mitigation: Update family-spec.csv and regenerate resonator drawings before cutting all) Tj T*
(tubes.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Structural Risks) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Arch cut-through or weak low bars) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Risk: C3 reaches the 0.250 in minimum center thickness.) Tj T*
(- Impact: Bass bars may crack, warp, or lose sustain.) Tj T*
(- Test: Measure remaining center thickness after CNC and after final sanding.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: No pilot bar falls below 0.250 in; no visible checking under normal strike) Tj T*
(force.) Tj T*
(- Mitigation: Increase minimum center thickness or choose denser/stiffer stock.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Support holes weaken bars) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Risk: 1/4 in holes near nodes may split if drilled too close to edges or with poor) Tj T*
(backing.) Tj T*
(- Impact: Cracks, buzzes, or support failure.) Tj T*
(- Test: Drill sample holes in offcuts and pilot bars with the intended bit and backing) Tj T*
(board.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: Clean holes with no breakout or splitting.) Tj T*
(- Mitigation: Reduce hole diameter, use cord grooves, or add rubber support posts instead.) Tj T*
