(final frame.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: Natural and accidental rows are reachable without shoulder strain for) Tj T*
(intended player.) Tj T*
(- Mitigation: Use a compact portable range, split frame, or revised bar spacing.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Supply Risks) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Padauk availability and quality) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Risk: Clear long Padauk stock may be expensive, unstable, or unavailable.) Tj T*
(- Impact: Build delays or inconsistent tone.) Tj T*
(- Test: Request current quotes and inspect board quality/moisture before purchase.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: Enough straight stock for 37 bars plus pilot failures.) Tj T*
(- Mitigation: Use hard maple/cherry for an education prototype and update material) Tj T*
(constants.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Tube/cap system mismatch) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Risk: Selected tube caps may leak, rattle, or be hard to tune.) Tj T*
(- Impact: Weak or noisy resonators.) Tj T*
(- Test: Build three tube prototypes with removable caps.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: Tubes hold adjustment and do not buzz under playing vibration.) Tj T*
(- Mitigation: Use adjustable stoppers, gasketed plugs, or alternate tube material.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Fit And Finish Risks) Tj T*
() Tj T*
( Finish shifts pitch or damps sustain) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Risk: A heavy finish adds mass and damping to tuned bars.) Tj T*
(- Impact: Bars go flat or lose sustain after finishing.) Tj T*
(- Test: Finish an offcut and one sacrificial tuned test bar; measure before/after Hz and) Tj T*
(decay.) Tj T*
(- Pass criterion: Pitch shift is predictable and within final tuning allowance.) Tj T*
